# Password Reset System — With Full Commands

## 1. Build and Run Spring Boot App

### Build using Apache Maven

```bash
mvn clean install
```

### Run the application

```bash
mvn spring-boot:run
```

OR

```bash
java -jar target/password-reset-app.jar
```

---

## 2. Run JUnit Tests

Using JUnit

```bash
mvn test
```

Run specific test:

```bash
mvn -Dtest=PasswordResetServiceTest test
```

---

## 3. GitHub Setup

Using GitHub

### Initialize repo

```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
```

### Connect to GitHub

```bash
git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/password-reset.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
```

---

## 4. CI Pipeline (GitHub Actions)

No command needed manually — triggers automatically on push.

### Trigger manually

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "trigger pipeline"
git push
```

---

## 5. Docker Commands

Using Docker

### Build Docker Image

```bash
docker build -t username/password-reset-app .
```

### Run Container

```bash
docker run -p 8080:8080 username/password-reset-app
```

### Check Running Containers

```bash
docker ps
```

### Stop Container

```bash
docker stop <container_id>
```

---

## 6. Push Image to Docker Hub

### Login

```bash
docker login
```

### Tag Image

```bash
docker tag password-reset-app username/password-reset-app
```

### Push Image

```bash
docker push username/password-reset-app
```

---

## 7. Kubernetes Commands

Using Kubernetes

### Apply Deployment

```bash
kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml
```

### Apply Service

```bash
kubectl apply -f service.yaml
```

### Check Resources

```bash
kubectl get pods
kubectl get services
kubectl get deployments
```

### Describe Pod (debugging)

```bash
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
```

### View Logs

```bash
kubectl logs <pod-name>
```

### Delete Deployment

```bash
kubectl delete -f deployment.yaml
```

---

## 8. Full CI/CD Flow (What Happens Automatically)

1. Code push to GitHub
2. GitHub Actions runs:

   * mvn clean install
   * mvn test
   * docker build
   * docker push
3. Kubernetes pulls latest image

---

## 9. Optional: Auto Deploy in Kubernetes

```bash
kubectl set image deployment/password-reset-app \
app=username/password-reset-app:latest
```

---

## 10. Real-World Dev Workflow

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "feature: OTP validation"
git push

kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml

kubectl get pods
```

